## How it fits together

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  CFG["workspace.config.yaml"] --> GEN[ai-workspace]
  GEN --> AG["AGENTS.md<br/>single source of truth"]
  AG --> CL["CLAUDE.md<br/>imports @AGENTS.md"]
  AG --> CO[".github/copilot-instructions.md<br/>generated mirror"]
  GEN --> MCP[".mcp.json / .vscode/mcp.json"]
  GEN --> IGN[".claudeignore / .copilotignore"]
<% if (it.sdd.enabled) { %>  GEN --> SDD["SDD methodology: openspec/ + /sdd-* commands (no external CLI)"]
<% } %><% if (it.livingDocs) { %>  GEN --> DOCS["docs/ai/*  ·  /doc-sync"]
<% } %>
```

## Daily use

> **You don't need to memorize commands.** Just describe what you want in chat — the AI detects the
> intent and applies the right flow (SDD, dependency assessment, commit, docs…). The commands below are
> optional manual shortcuts.

- **Edit rules** in `AGENTS.md`, then run `ai-workspace sync` (regenerates adapters, preserves your edits outside markers).
- **Add a stack module:** `ai-workspace add <module>`.
- **Upgrade templates:** `ai-workspace upgrade` (shows a diff first).
- **Check health:** `ai-workspace doctor` (token budgets, broken refs).
<% if (it.sdd.enabled) { %>- **Plan a change:** `/sdd-explore` → `/sdd-propose` → `/sdd-clarify` → … → `/sdd-archive` (a methodology — artifacts are Markdown in `openspec/`, no external CLI).
<% } %><% if (it.livingDocs) { %>- **Refresh project state for the AI:** `/doc-sync`.
<% } %>

## Governance & commits
- **Project mode:** <%= it.project.mode %> — <%= it.project.mode === "existing" ? "conservative versions; upgrade only via assessment" : "current stable versions" %>.
- **Commits:** <%= it.workflow.commits.coAuthor ? "with" : "no" %> co-author trailers; <%= it.workflow.commits.automate === "with-approval" ? "committed only after your approval (use /commit)" : "manual (you commit)" %>.
- **Safety gate:** the AI must stop and ask before version bumps, migrations, conflicts or risky changes.
<% if (it.workflow.commits.gitHook) { %>- **Enforcement:** activate the commit hook once → `git config core.hooksPath .githooks`
<% } %>
## Scope & ignore
- **Excluded from AI context** (`.claudeignore` / `.copilotignore`): <%= it.scope.ignore.join(", ") %>
- **Git-ignored (not shared):** <%= it.scope.gitignoreManaged.join(", ") %>
- Everything else under `.claude/`, `.github/`, `docs/ai/`, `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md` and
  `workspace.config.yaml` is **committed** so the whole team shares the same AI setup.
